==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Picul
<hw>Pic"ul</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Jav. & Malay
<ets>pikul</ets>, fr. <ets>pikul</ets> to carry on the back, to carry a
burden; n., a man's burden.]</ety> <def>A commercial weight varying in
different countries and for different commodities. In Borneo it is
135⟦frac58⟧ lbs.; in China and Sumatra, 133⟦frac12⟧ lbs.; in Japan,
133⟦frac13⟧ lbs.; but sometimes 130 lbs., etc. Called also, by the
Chinese, <altname>tan</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>pecul</asp>, and <asp>pecal</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piculet</ent>⟦br⟧
